question: what does aa on a license plate mean
vanilla_rag_result: In the context of the passages provided, "aa" on a license plate refers to the two-letter suffix used in the registration plates for buses, coaches, and commercially owned or run mini-buses in Victoria, Australia. These plates use a four-number, two-letter format (nnnn-"aa"), where "aa" represents specific registration categories such as accredited operator (AO), accredited charter (AC), school operator (SO), or non-commercial (NC).
